#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:12
msgid "Freehand Brush"
msgstr "フリーハンドブラシ"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:12
msgid "Freehand"
msgstr "フリーハンド"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:17
msgid "Freehand Brush Tool"
msgstr "フリーハンドブラシツール"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:19
msgid "|toolfreehandbrush|"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:21
msgid "The default tool you have selected on Krita start-up, and likely the tool that you will use the most."
msgstr "Krita が起動したときに選択されている既定のツールで、おそらく最も使用する頻度が高いものでしょう。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:23
msgid ""
"The freehand brush tool allows you to paint on paint layers without constraints like the straight line tool. It makes optimal use of your tablet's input settings to control the brush-appearance. To "
"switch the brush, make use of the brush-preset docker."
msgstr "フリーハンドブラシツールは直線ツールのような制約なくペイントレイヤーに描けるツールです。ブラシの見た目を変えるタブレット入力設定としては最も良い使い方です。ブラシを変えるには、ブラシプリセットドッカーを使用します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:27
msgid "Hotkeys and Sticky keys"
msgstr "ホットキーとスティッキーキー"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:29
msgid "The freehand brush tool's hotkey is :kbd:`B`."
msgstr "フリーハンドブラシツールのホットキーは :kbd:`B` です。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:31
msgid ""
"The alternate invocation is the ''color sampler'' (standardly invoked by the :kbd:`Ctrl` key). Press the :kbd:`Ctrl` key to switch the tool to \"color sampler\", use left or right click to sample "
"fore and background color respectively. Release the :kbd:`Ctrl` key to return to the freehand brush tool."
msgstr "ここで他に呼び出せるものは''スポイト''です(通常 :kbd:`Ctrl` キーで呼び出します)。:kbd:`Ctrl` キーで\"スポイト\"ツールに切り替え、右、左クリックでそれぞれ背景色と描画色を取ります。:kbd:`Ctrl` キーを離すとフリーハンドブラシツールに戻ります。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:32
msgid "The Primary setting is \"size\" (standardly invoked by the :kbd:`Shift` key). Press the :kbd:`Shift` key and drag outward to increase brush size. Drag inward to decrease it."
msgstr "次の設定は\"サイズ\"です(通常 :kbd:`Shift` キーで呼び出します)。:kbd:`Shift` を押して外側にドラッグすることでブラシサイズを上げます。内側にすると下げます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:33
msgid "You can also press the :kbd:`V` key as a stickykey for the straight-line tool."
msgstr "また :kbd:`V` キーを押すことで直線ツールになります。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:35
msgid ""
"The hotkey can be edited in :menuselection:`Settings --> Configure Krita... --> Shortcuts`. The sticky-keys can be edited in :menuselection:`Settings --> Configure Krita... --> Canvas Input "
"Settings`."
msgstr ":menuselection:`設定 --> Krita の設定を変更... --> ショートカット` からホットキーを編集できます。スティッキーキーは :menuselection:`設定 --> Krita の設定を変更... --> キャンバス入力の設定` から編集します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:39
msgid "Tool Options"
msgstr "ツールのオプション"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:41 ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:82
msgid "Stabilizer"
msgstr "スタビライザー"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:41
msgid "Basic Smooth"
msgstr "基本"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:41
msgid "No Smoothing"
msgstr "なし"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:41
msgid "Weighted Smoothing"
msgstr "重み付け"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:45
msgid "Smoothing"
msgstr "手振れ補正"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:47
msgid "Smoothing, also known as stabilising in some programs, allows the program to correct the stroke. Useful for people with shaky hands, or particularly difficult long lines."
msgstr "手振れ補正、またはプログラムによりスムーズ化やスタビライズとして知られ、ストロークの補正をすることができます。手が震える人や、長い線を描く際に便利です。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:49
msgid "The following options can be selected:"
msgstr "次のオプションが選べます:"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:51
msgid "No Smoothing."
msgstr "なし"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:52
msgid "The input from the tablet translates directly to the screen. This is the fastest option, and good for fine details."
msgstr "タブレットの入力が直接画面に変換されます。これが最も早いオプションで、細部を描く際に良いです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:53
msgid "Basic Smoothing."
msgstr "基本"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:54
msgid ""
"This option will smooth the input of older tablets like the Wacom Graphire 3. If you experience slightly jagged lines without any smoothing on, this option will apply a very little bit of smoothing "
"to get rid of those lines."
msgstr "Wacom Graphire 3と言った古いタブレットの入力をスムーズにします。もしスムーズ化なしで線画がガタガタになるときに、このオプションを使うと少し良くなります。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:56
msgid "This option allows you to use the following parameters to make the smoothing stronger or weaker:"
msgstr "このオプションは次のパラメーターを使ってスムーズ化を強くしたり弱くしたりできます:"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:58
msgid "Distance"
msgstr "遅延"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:59
msgid "The distance the brush needs to move before the first dab is drawn. (Literally the amount of events received by the tablet before the first dab is drawn.)"
msgstr "最初の点が描かれる前にブラシが動かないといけない距離です。(文字どおり最初の点が描かれる前にタブレットが受け取るイベントの数です。)"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:60
msgid "Stroke Ending"
msgstr "はらいの長さ"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:61
msgid ""
"This controls how much the line will attempt to reach the last known position of the cursor after the left-mouse button/or stylus is lifted. Will currently always result in a straight line, so use "
"with caution."
msgstr "マウス左ボタン/またはスタイラスペンが持ち上げられた跡にそのカーソルの場所まで描こうとするかを操作できます。今のところ常に直線になるので、使用する場合は注意してください。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:62
msgid "Smooth Pressure"
msgstr "筆圧の変化を滑らかにする"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:63
msgid "This will apply the smoothing on the pressure input as well, resulting in more averaged size for example."
msgstr "筆圧入力もスムーズ化するようになり、例えばサイズもより平均的になります。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:65
msgid "Weighted smoothing:"
msgstr "重み付け:"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:65 ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:82
msgid "Scalable Distance"
msgstr "表示倍率に合わせる"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:65 ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:83
msgid "This makes it so that the numbers involved will be scaled along the zoom level."
msgstr "ズームレベルに合わせて各数値を調整するようになります。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:68
msgid ""
"This option averages all inputs from the tablet. It is different from weighted smoothing in that it allows for always completing the line. It will draw a circle around your cursor and the line will "
"be a bit behind your cursor while painting."
msgstr "このオプションはタブレットからのすべての入力を平均化します。重み付けが常に線を最後まで描くという点では異なります。カーソルの周りに円が現れ描いている間はカーソルより少し後ろに線が引かれます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:70
msgid "distance is replaced by smoothing at max and min speed."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:72
msgid "Sample Count at Max Speed"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:73
msgid ""
"This is the strength of the smoothing when drawing as fast as possible. For the best results, set it much lower than that of min speed. The idea being that a fast stroke needs less smoothing than a "
"slow stroke."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:74
msgid "Sample Count at Min Speed"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:75
msgid "This is the strength of the smoothing when drawing as slow as possible. For best results, this one can be set much higher than that of max speed."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:76
msgid "Delay"
msgstr "遅延"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:77
msgid "This toggles and determines the size of the dead zone around the cursor. This can be used to create sharp corners with more control."
msgstr "カーソル周りにあるデッドゾーンの切り替えやそのサイズを変更します。よりシャープな角を作る際に使用できます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:78
msgid "Finish Line"
msgstr "最後まで描画"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:79
msgid "This ensures that the line will be finished."
msgstr "線を最後まで描くようにします。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:80
msgid "Stabilize sensors"
msgstr "各センサーからの数値を安定化"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:81
msgid "Similar to :guilabel:`Smooth Pressure`, this allows the input (pressure, speed, tilt) to be smoother."
msgstr ":guilabel:`筆圧の変化を滑らかにする` によく似ていて、入力(筆圧、速度、回転)をよりスムーズにします。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:85
msgid "Keeps lines drawn with a single-pixel brush at single-pixel width, avoiding L-shaped corners or doubling-up of pixels."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:89
msgid "Left: result without smoothing. Right: result with :guilabel:`Pixel` smoothing."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:91
msgid "Pixel"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:93
msgid "Painting Assistants"
msgstr "補助線"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:96
msgid "Assistants"
msgstr "補助線にスナップ"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:98
msgid "Ticking this will allow snapping to :ref:`assistant_tool`, and the hotkey to toggle it is :kbd:`Ctrl + Shift + L`. See :ref:`painting_with_assistants` for more information."
msgstr "これをオンにすると :ref:`assistant_tool` にスナップするようになります。:kbd:`Ctrl + Shift + L` のホットキーで切り替えができます。詳しい情報は :ref:`painting_with_assistants` を見てください。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:100
msgid ""
"The slider will determine the amount of snapping, with 1000 being perfect snapping, and 0 being no snapping at all. For situations where there is more than one assistant on the canvas, the defaultly"
" ticked :guilabel:`Snap Single` means that Krita will only snap to a single assistant at a time, preventing noise. Unticking it allows you to chain assistants together and snap along them."
msgstr "スライダーでスナップする量を決めることができ、1000で完全にスナップ、0で何もスナップしなくなります。キャンバス上に2つ以上の補助線がある場合、:guilabel:`1つの補助線にのみスナップ` で同時に他の補助線にスナップしなくなり、わずらわしさがなくなります。チェックを外すとそれらの補助線にもスナップするようになります。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/tools/freehand_brush.rst:102
msgid ""
"You may not always want erasers to snap, especially when using assistants liberally during the sketching process. :guilabel:`Snap Eraser` will allow you to turn off snapping for brushes with the "
"blending mode :ref:`bm_erase`."
msgstr ""

